The Deputy Chief Executive of Geregu Power Plc, Julius Omodayo-Owotuga, has joined the board of FBN Holdings Plc as a non-executive director following the approval of his appointment by the Central Bank of Nigeria. A statement said Omodayo-Owotuga was previously the group executive director, finance and risk management at Forte Oil Plc (now Ardova Plc). According to the statement, he is a finance expert with huge experience in finance, risk management, treasury, internal controls, general administration, procurement, and information technology. It said, “While at Forte, he was a member of the Executive Management Team that restructured a then moribund company into a vibrant industry player. He equally led the capital restructuring, acquisitions, debt capital raise, maiden credit rating and divestment initiatives. Prior to joining Forte Oil Plc, he had responsibility for the asset and liabilities management function at the Africa Finance Corporation. “He is a KPMG trained finance professional who possesses extensive investment experience spanning financial services, power and oil and gas sectors with a proven track record of significant achievements. His two decades work experience spans blue-chip companies such as KPMG, Standard Chartered Bank, Africa Finance Corporation, Forte Oil Plc, MBC International Bank (now First Bank of Nigeria Limited) and Geregu Power Plc.” According to the statement, he is an alumnus of Oxford University’s Said Business School, United Kingdom, IE Business School, Madrid, Spain and the University of Lagos, Lagos, Nigeria.